  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> \\( a^m \\times a^n = a^{mn} \\) (multiply the indices)</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Multiplying powers of the same base ADDS the indices. A weak answer multiplies; a strong answer writes \\( a^m \\times a^n = a^{m+n} \\), keeping the power-of-a-power rule separate.</p>",
  "question": "Simplify \\( x^2 \\times x^5 \\).",
