  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> \\( 8^{2/3} = 8 \\times \\frac{2}{3} = \\frac{16}{3} \\)</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> A fractional index is a root and a power, not a multiplier. A weak answer multiplies the base by the fraction; a strong answer takes the root first: \\( \\left(\\sqrt[3]{8}\\right)^2 = 2^2 = 4 \\).</p>",
