  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> \\( x^2 + 6x - 11 = (x+6)^2 - 11 \\)</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> You must HALVE the coefficient of \\( x \\): it is \\( (x+3)^2 \\), not \\( (x+6)^2 \\). A weak answer copies the 6; a strong answer writes \\( (x+3)^2 - 9 - 11 = (x+3)^2 - 20 \\).</p>",
