  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> \\( (4x^2 - 2x + 3) - (x^2 - 5x + 1) = 3x^2 - 7x + 2 \\)</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> The minus applies to EVERY term in the second bracket. A weak answer only negates the first term; a strong answer writes \\( 4x^2 - 2x + 3 - x^2 + 5x - 1 = 3x^2 + 3x + 2 \\).</p>",
  "question": "\\( (4x^2 - 2x + 3) - (x^2 - 5x + 1) = ? \\)",
