  "pageId": "additional-maths:2-3-setting-up-and-solving-equations",
  "pageName": "2.3 Setting Up and Solving Equations",
  "source": "tips",
  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "tip — Reject the impossible root",
  "reading": "<p>Every quadratic or cubic from a context can throw up a root that cannot happen — a negative length, a negative speed, a fractional person. Write the rejected root down and say <strong>why</strong>: \"reject \\( x = -8 \\) as a width cannot be negative.\" Silently dropping it can still lose the reasoning mark.</p>",
  "question": "When you reject a root you should:",
