  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Trying to generate \\( x_{n+2} = x_{n+1} + x_n \\) from a single starting value.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> A second-order rule needs two terms to start. A weak answer stalls with only \\( x_1 \\); a strong answer uses both \\( x_1 \\) and \\( x_2 \\), then builds \\( x_3 = x_2 + x_1 \\).</p>",
